<TITLE> Polls schedule this evening: CEC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moinul Hoque Chowdhury bdnews24.com correspondent Dhaka, Nov 2 (bdnews24.com)  The Election Commission is set to declare the schedule for general election on Sunday evening, on the back of a High Court ruling on demarcation in the EC's favour, the chief election commissioner said. "The schedule for national elections will be declared in the evening," ATM Shamsul Huda told bdnews24.com on Sunday afternoon. EC officials said the polls chief would declare the election date, deadline of submission and scrutiny of nomination papers, and date for withdrawal of nomination papers in TV, radio address to the nation at 7:30pm. The HC earlier in the day dismissed three separate writ petitions challenging the EC's gazette on the demarcation of parliamentary seats, which lawyers said cleared the way for announcement of the election schedule. The EC sat in an emergency meeting after the HC ruling. The commission was originally set to declare the schedule on Nov 2 (Sunday), but was awaiting the High Court verdict. "We are relieved, as are the voting public. The commission now will decide the next move," Muhammad Sohul Hussain told reporters in an immediate reaction to the ruling. "The election schedule will be announced any day," Sohul told bdnews24.com before entering the meeting. Asked whether the schedule would be declared on Sunday, he said that the commission would let it be known after the meeting concluded. bdnews24.
